  "title": "Electrical Engineer (Ref 26325)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Perform diagnostic checks and troubleshooting for electrical and electromechanical systems (e.g., power distribution, control systems, wiring harnesses).<br />• Carry out hands-on repair and maintenance of electrical components and systems.<br />• Conduct engineering studies and analysis for military electrical systems.<br />• Work with internal teams and local industry to develop local repair capability for electrical equipment.<br />• Prepare and maintain electrical system specifications, design documents, and technical reports.<br />• Ensure compliance with industry standards and regulations, including electrical safety standards.<br /><br />Requirements<br />• Bachelor’s degree in electrical engineering or other relevant disciplines (e.g., Electronics, Mechatronics, Power Engineering).<br />• Minimum 2 year of working experience.<br />• Strong understanding of electrical engineering principles and practices.<br />• Proficient in report writing and good presentation skills to stakeholders at all levels<br />• Knowledge of electrical design tools and CAD software is an advantage.<br />• Able to interact well with internal teams and customers.<br /></p><p>Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
